%N A393481 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k) + Omega(k)^8.
%C A393481 a(3) > 10^10, if it exists. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 14 2026
%e A393481 4285700 is a term since sigma(4285700) = 9850932 = 8171280 + 36 + 6^8 = psi(4285700) + tau(4285700) + Omega(4285700)^8.
%o A393481 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f) + bigomega(f)^8; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 13 2026
